UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/002219969190054A
AB  - The paper shows the existence of a case for protection in a small open economy in which there is preference diversity and potential product differentation with scale economies. The optimal tariff gives partial protection only, is a first-best solution, and must be sustained. The welfare loss that is corrected by the tariff is that due to a sub-optimal degree of product variety, arising from market failure linked to economies of scale.
ER  - 

